com.siperian.sif.message.metadata

Class MetaDataHmConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.metadata.MetaDataBase
      • com.siperian.sif.message.metadata.MetaDataHmConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable

    public class MetaDataHmConfiguration
extends MetaDataBase
    Represents HM configuration. It contains information about the composition of the HM configuration including the following:
    • Profile
    • Sandbox
    • Hierarchies
    • Entity Types
    • Relationship Types
    • Packages
    This class is also used to construct tool tips and labels for entities and relationships.
    See Also:
    DescribeSiperianObjectRequest, Serialized Form

    API Group: Metadata

      • getHmPackage

        public MetaDataHmPackage getHmPackage(String typeUid,
                                      String usageType)
        Get the MetaDataHmPackage object associated with this configuration that has the specified type UID and usage type. Usage type should be one of the MetaDataHmPackage.PKG_USAGE_TYPE_* values.
        Parameters:
        typeUid - - UID of the entity type / relationship type for which the HM package is needed.
        usageType - - Usage type of the HM package needed.
        Returns:
        HM Package with the specified usage type associated with the specified entity type / relationship type. Can be null.

      • getHmPackageColumnUids

        public List getHmPackageColumnUids(String typeUid,
                                   String usageType)
        Get the List of column UIDs associated with this configuration that are contained in the MetaDataHmPackage that has the specified type UID and usage type. Usage type should be one of the MetaDataHmPackage.PKG_USAGE_TYPE_* values.
        Parameters:
        typeUid - - UID of the entity type / relationship type for which the HM package columns are needed.
        usageType - - Usage type of the HM package whose columns are needed. Should be one of MetaDataHmPackage.PKG_USAGE_TYPE_* values.
        Returns:
        A List of Column UIDs (String objects) in the order of their sequence in this HM package. Can be empty but never null.

      • createTooltip

        public String createTooltip(Record record)
        Return a String that is the tool tip for the specified entity or relationship record.
        Parameters:
        record - - Record for which the tool tip is needed. Record MUST be an entity or relationship from GetEntityGraphResponse or GetOneHopResponse or SearchHmQueryResponse. This is because we use the SiperianObjectUid from the record to determine the entity type / relationship type.
        Returns:
        The tool tip String for the record. In case of an error, we return an empty String instead of throwing an exception because this method will probably be called many times in a single user interaction e.g. when the user is shown a bunch of entities and relationships from One-Hop request

      • createLabel

        public String createLabel(Record record)
        Return a String that is the label for the specified entity record. Relationship records do not have labels.
        Parameters:
        record - - Record for which the label is needed. Record MUST be an entity from GetEntityGraphResponse or GetOneHopResponse or SearchHmQueryResponse. This is because we use the SiperianObjectUid from the record to determine the entity type.
        Returns:
        The label String for the record. In case of an error, we return an empty String instead of throwing an exception because this method will probably be called many times in a single user interaction e.g. when the user is shown a bunch of entities from One-Hop request

      • getRelTypesForEntityTypes

        public List getRelTypesForEntityTypes(MetaDataHmEntityType entType1,
                                      MetaDataHmEntityType entType2,
                                      boolean allowReverse)
        Get the List of relationship types that involve the specified entities.
        Parameters:
        entType1 - - The MetaDataHmEntityType for the first entity of the relationship
        entType2 - - The MetaDataHmEntityType for the second entity of the relationship
        allowReverse - - if true, the entity types specified can be in any order in the relationship type. If false, the order of entity types in the relationship type has to match the order specified in the method call.
        Returns:
        List of MetaDataHmRelationshipType objects that can be used for specified entity types.

      • getRelTypesForEntityTypes

        public List getRelTypesForEntityTypes(String entTypeUid1,
                                      String entTypeUid2,
                                      boolean allowReverse)
        Get the List of relationship types that involve the specified entities.
        Parameters:
        entTypeUid1 - - entity type UID
        entTypeUid2 - - entity type UID
        allowReverse - - if true, the entity types specified can be in any order in the relationship type. If false, the order of entity types in the relationship type has to match the order specified in the method call.
        Returns:
        List of MetaDataHmRelationshipType objects that can be used for specified entity types.
